There are 2 ways to do this:

 1. Multiple Value Parameter:
First of all, you must use Oracle provider, multiple value paramaters does not work with neither ODBC nor OLEDB connections ([reference](https://social.msdn.microsoft.com/Forums/sqlserver/en-US/31c1ab35-2b78-4d30-9fec-7c95e1cd7d0a/multi-value-parameters-in-ssrs-with-oracle-database?forum=sqlreportingservices)).
 Here is an external link explaining in detail [here](https://arcanecode.com/2008/10/20/sql-server-reporting-services-oracle-and-multivalued-parameters/).

 2. Using an expression as the query by putting the whole thing like this ```=&quot;query_here&quot;```
```
